dspace-development.title: Authentication attempts over Shibboleth for DataSpace and the OAR yield `Web Login Service - Stale Request` errors

comments.body:
The following configuration setting for `relayd` was primarily affecting this:

```conf
# filters
http protocol httpsfilter {
# [...]
    match response header set "Cache-Control" value "max-age=$VALUE"
# [...]
```

Further, there were some adjustments to the `shibd`, `nginx`, and `httpd` configuration, but this may simply have improved performance.
I must draft some more definitive information for this, but there is a meeting later today with a user who experienced problems which might have some additional information.

marc_liberation.title: Add notes in the get_items_for_bib method
Redirect links with voyager IDs to their equivalent alma id endpoint

comments.body: Essentially, it is unknown how many external sites (like professor's blogs, LibGuides, etc.) use direct links to Blacklight bib records, so there needs to be a redirect in place to take a user from a Voyager bib ID to the new Alma MMS ID.

Do we want to inspect the ID? or do we want to just try a rewrite if the page isn't found?

A voyager bib id will always be numeric. There is no maximum length, but we could get the last id used in voyager (13million would be the highest). The minimum length of an alma id would be the prefix and suffix with 1 in between.
